# Function to extract numeric values from a string
def extract_numeric(value):
    match = re.search(r'\d+', str(value))
    return int(match.group()) if match else None

# Apply the extraction function to 'Age' column
cleaned_df['Age'] = cleaned_df['Age'].apply(extract_numeric)

# Keep only the values in 'Age' between 0 and 150

from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, accuracy_score

# Confusion Matrix Heatmap Function
def plot_confusion_matrix(cm, title, labels):
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=labels, yticklabels=labels)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.ylabel('True')
    plt.show()

# Plot Confusion Matrices for each Classifier
plot_confusion_matrix(kn_cm, 'KNN Classifier Confusion Matrix', labels=df_cleaned['Credit_Score'].unique())
plot_confusion_matrix(svc_cm, 'SVC Classifier Confusion Matrix', labels=df_cleaned['Credit_Score'].unique())
plot_confusion_matrix(rf_cm, 'Random Forest Classifier Confusion Matrix', labels=df_cleaned['Credit_Score'].unique())

# Plot Accuracy Scores
classifiers = ['KNN Classifier', 'SVC Classifier', 'Random Forest Classifier']
accuracy_scores = [kn_accuracy, svc_accuracy, rf_accuracy]

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(x=classifiers, y=accuracy_scores, palette='viridis')
plt.title('Accuracy Scores of Classifiers')
plt.ylim(0, 1)  # Set y-axis limit to ensure a proper scale
plt.show()
